Some Probability problems
	- Problem: Fair single dice probability. Sample space: {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6}. Odd/even events probability.
	- Problem: Two dice probability. Sample space: {2, 3, 4, ..., 11, 12}. Odd/even events probability.
	- Problem: Birthday problem: Probability of two people in a room sharing birthday.
	- Problem: Poker problem: Probability of players getting a pair of cards.


Probabilidade Binomial
	- Problem: Qual a probabilidade que em 6 jogadas de dados, temos sempre numeros diferentes?
	- Example: 6 tosses of unfair coin.
		- P(H) = p. Independent event.
		- Calc: Probabilidade de P(HTTHHH)
		- Calc: Probabilidade de P(HHTTHH)
		- Note: Same probability.
	- Generalization: Sequencia de n lançamentos
		- Probabilidade da sequencia de n lançamentos
		- Calc: P(k heads)
		- Calc: P(k tails)
	- Problem: Coin Tossing Problem
		P(H) = p. Independent.
		- Event B: 3 out of 10 tosses were heads
		- Event A: First tosses are heads.
		- Compute: P(A|B)
		- Computing: |B| and |A inter B|.
	- Partition Problem
		- Partição de 52 cartas de baralho para 4 players.
		- Compute: Probability to get 4 aces each.
	- System reliability probability
		- System has n-identical pieces. Only works if at least k of them works.
		- Calc: Probability of system failure.
		- Calc: Probability of system is operational.
	- Example: Power station
		- City has n power stations. Failure probability is pi.
		- Calc: At least 1 plant can supply the city. Probability of black-out in the city.
		- Calc: At least 2 plants can supply the city. Probability of black-out in the city.
		- Calc: At least k plants can supply the city. Probability of black-out in the city.


Probabilidade Condicional
	- Intuitive calculation of conditioning
		- Equaly likely dice.
		- Compute: P(6 outcome | even outcome)
	- Motivation for definition
		- Condicionamento: B occured
		- Opt 01: Probabilidade da intersecção with new normalization: New sample space.
		- Opt 02: Manter proporção entre probabilidades
	- Formal Definition
		- Definition
		- Def: P(A|B)
		- Note: Simetria entre P(A inter B) = P(B inter A)
		- Calc: P(A|B) / P(B|A)
		- Intuition: For P(A|B), B is now the sample space
	- Theorem: Conditional probability is a probability
		- Must satisfy all probability axioms (def of probability)
		- Nonnegativity (trivial).
		- Normalization: P(sample | B) = 1.
		- Aditivity: P(A u B | C) = P(A|C) + P(B|C) (for disjoint sets A,B).
	- Since is probability, properties is inherited
		- Proof: Inequação de Boole para probabilidade condicional.
		- Equação para inequação de boole, para probabilidade condicional
		- Discrete Probability Law.
		- Discrete Uniform Probability Law.
	- Propriedades exclusivas
		- Compute: P(B|B) = 1. As expected.
		- Compute: P(A|sample) = P(A). As expected.
		- Note: Probabilidade condicional é indefinido se P(B) = 0. As expected.
		- Intuition: P(A|B), B is now new "sample space".
	- Example: Three sucessive coin tosses
		- Condition: 1st toss is head
		- Calc: Probability of having more H than T.
	- Example: Experiment: Jogar dois dados X, Y, de 4 lados each
		- Assumption: Every possible outcome has same probability. B = min(X,Y)
		- Calc: P(M=1 | B)
		- Calc: P(M=2 | B)
		- Calc: P(min(X,Y)=2)
		- Intuition: Probabilidade condicional
	- Example: Radar detector
		- Event A: Airplane is flying above
		- Event B: Something register on radar screen
		- Specs: P(A)=0.05. P(B|Ac) = 0.10. P(B|A) = 0.99.
		- Montando árvore de probabilidade
			- Paths: Probabilities
			- Leak: Events.
		- Compute: P(Ac int B)
		- Compute: P(A int Bc)
		- Question: Is this a reliable and nice radar? Would you buy it?
	- Probabilidade condicional de interseções
		- Visualização in decision tree
			- Prove: P(A int B) = P(A) P(B|A).
			- Prove: P(A int B) = P(B) P(A|B).
			- Note: Moving in foward/backward in the tree
		- Conditional tree
			- Note: Foward: P(A int B | C) = P(A|C) P(B|A int C).
			- Note: Backward: P(A int B | C) = P(B|C) P(A|B int C).
			- Proof: Foward formula.
			- Proof: Backward formula.
	- Regra da multiplicação
		- Theorem: P(A int B int C) = P(A) P(B|A) P(C | A int B)
		- Intuition: Calculo de probabilidade de caminhos de tree
		- Generalização para n eventos
	- Total Probability Theorem: P(B) = sum P(Ai) P(B|Ai)
		- Proof for n=2. Divisão de sample em A e A'.
		- Partição de sample space em conjuntos disjuntos Ai.
		- Proof of the theorem
		- Note: Media ponderada de probabilidade condicional em cada partição.
		- Visualização em eventos (conjuntos).
		- Visualização no tree
	- Bayes' Rules
		- Prior Probabilities: P(Ai)
		- Know: P(B|Ai).
		- Calc: P(Ai|B) em função de P(B|Ai) e P(B)
		- Calc: P(Ai|B) em função de P(B|Ai) e P(Ai)
		- Note: Cause --> Effect. P(B|Ai).
		- Note: Effect --> Cause. Inference! P(Ai|B)
	- Example: Back to radar detection.
		- Event A: Airplane is flying above
		- Event B: Something register on radar screen
		- Identifying cause and effect.
		- Specs: P(A)=0.05. P(B|Ac) = 0.10. P(B|A) = 0.99.
		- Tree de eventos
		- General Inference: Given effect what was probability of cause?
		- Inference: Given radar register something, probability has plane on skies?
		- Question: Is this a reliable and nice radar? Would you buy it?
		- Note: Non-intuitive phenomena may appear, as you can see.
	- Example: 95%-correct test for desease detection.
		- Patiente has desease, test result positive in 95%.
		- Patiente has not desease, test result negative in 95%.
		- It's a rare desease. 0.1% of proboability random guy has it.
		- Inference: Given tested positive, probability has the desease?
		- Question: Is this a reliable test?
	- The Example: Monty Hall Problem
		- Description of the problem.
		- What is the best tactic to employ?
		- Calculations.
		- Intuition: Exageration: 100 doors.


Eventos Independentes
	- Example: Jogada de moeda. P(H) = p. P(T) = 1-p.
		- Fazendo árvore de probabilidade
		- Identificar probabilidades condicionais (branch of the tree)
		- Calc: P(THT).
		- Calc: P(1 head)
		- Calc Intuitively: P(First toss is H | 1 head)
		- Calc: P(First toss is H | 1 head)
		- Note: Intuition is ok
		- Note: Jogada antes não alterou o que aconteceria depois
	- Formal Definition: Independency
		- Def: P(B|A) = P(B)
			- Interpretation of def.
			- Note: Def makes no sense if P(A) = 0
		- Formal Def: P(A inter B) = P(A)P(B)
			- Note: Def now makes sense if P(A) = 0.
			- Proof: P(A inter B) = P(A)P(B) ==> P(B|A) = P(B)
		- Note: If A is independent of B ==> B is independent of A. Symmetry!
	- Example: Coin and rain.
		- Probability of Heads, Tails, and Rain, NotRain.
		- Visualization in a tree. Identify conditional probabilities.
		- Note: Independent events.
	- Example: Eventos disjuntos
		- Intuition: Is this dependent or independent?
		- Formally: Is this depedent or independent?
			- Using def 1
			- Using formal def
		- Note: Case of definitly dependence
	- Visualization: Quando eventos são independentes
		- Visually: Desenho de eventos
		- Visually: Desenho de árvore de probabilidade
	- Theorem: A, B independentes <==> A, Bc independentes.
	- Independencia condicional entre dois eventos
		- Conditional events are probability. So...
		- Formal definition
		- Equivalent Definition usando regra da multiplicação
			- P(A | B int C) = P(A|C)
		- Discussion of what is going on in both definitions
		- Comparison with non-conditional independency
	- Conditioning may affect independency
		- Visually: Desenho de eventos
		- Assume: Conjuntos A, B independentes.
		- Eventos ainda será independentes se forem condicionados a C?
	- Example: Chosing and tossing coins
		- Visualização usando árvore de probabilidade
		- Is events independent?
		- Is event independent conditionally we know the coin A/B ?
		- Intuition: P(toss 11 = H)
		- Formally: P(toss 11 = H)
		- Intuition: P(toss 11 = H | first 10 are head)
		- Formally: P(toss 11 = H | first 10 are head)
	- Mutual and pairwise independency
		- Motivation (visualizing tree) of independence of n events.
		- Formal Definition: Mutual independency between n events. (Or simply independence)
		- Formal Definition: Pairwise independency between n events.
		- Theorem: Pairwise Independency does not imply Mutual Independency
		- Theorem: Mutual Independency ==> Pairwise independency (by definition, trivial)


Discrete Random Variables
	- Example: Intuitive Definition
	- Formal Definition and Notation
	- Simple Example of Random Variables
		- Altura de alunos
		- Iteração de função (de random Variable)
		- Note: The Notation :)
	- Função Massa de Probabilidade: Probability Mass Function (PMF)
		- Formal Definition
		- Example: P(H) = p. X = Number of coin tosses until first head
			- Calculating X for different outcomes
			- Note: X is cleary a random variable
			- Calc: Função massa de probabilidade
			- Grafico de barras da função massa de probabilidade
			- Def: PMF Geométrica
		- Example: Two Independent rolls of a fair tetrahedral die
			- F: Outcome in first throw
			- S: Outcome in second Throw
			- X = min(F, S)
			- Note: F, S, X are cleary random variables
			- Calc: Px(2)
			- Grafico de barras da função massa de probabilidade
		- Example: Coin Tossing problem: Probabilidade binomial
			- X = Having k heads/tails in the outcome
			- Função massa de probabilidade
			- Grafico de barras da função massa de probabilidade
	- Expectation. Expected Value.
		- Intuition: Example: Following game: P(x) = probability of getting x dollars
			- P(1) = 1/6.  P(2) = 1/2.  P(4) = 1/3.
			- On average, how many will you receive playing n times?
			- Note: Calculation we just did, in formal way is...
		- Formal Definition of Expectation (Expected Value)
		- Interpretation: Center of Mass


